        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 25 at 5:57PM EDT by NWS Chicago IL</headline>
        <description>At 557 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Boswell, or 10 miles south of Fowler, moving east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Templeton, Boswell, Oxford, and Otterbein.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
